{
  "texts": [
    "1 An injury related to running is characterized by musculoskeletal discomfort in the lower limbs, which hampers or prevents running activities such as distance, speed, duration, or training.",
    "Running-related injuries (RRI) predominantly impact the distal region of the lower limb, with approximately 70% of cases occurring at or below the knee.",
    "The most prevalent RRIs were found to be plantar fasciitis, iliotibial band syndrome, patellofemoral pain, and Achilles tendonitis after a comprehensive review of nine publications.",
    "RRI has an impact on event planning and is linked to financial hardship, psychological discomfort, and a decrease in the desire to resume running.",
    "2 The most frequent disorder causing knee discomfort is patellofemoral syndrome (runner's knee)."
  ]
}